                "value": "Not all debt is equal. 'Good debt' (like a mortgage or student loan) can build long-term value, while 'bad debt' (like high-interest credit card debt) can quickly spiral. Two popular payoff strategies are the debt snowball (pay smallest balances first) and debt avalanche (pay highest interest rates first)."
